
Overview of noun alkali

The noun alkali has 2 senses (first 1 from tagged texts)
                                         
1. (3) base, alkali -- (any of various water-soluble compounds capable of turning litmus blue and reacting with an acid to form a salt and water; "bases include oxides and hydroxides of metals and ammonia")
2. alkali -- (a mixture of soluble salts found in arid soils and some bodies of water; detrimental to agriculture)
